  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>South Facing Eiger Rooms</strong> are located in the main building. They sleep two people with an Austrian Twin bed and are south facing with a balcony. These rooms can be used for sole use for a supplement, on request - please call us to book.</p>
<p><strong>Crystal Annexe South Facing Twin Rooms</strong> are located in the Crystal Annexe across the road from the main building. These newly renovated rooms are on the upper floors and have a south facing balcony. They have a bath or shower and can sleep up to three (extra bed is a single bed).</p>
<p>The Crystal Annexe is located opposite the main building.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Bath or shower</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>General information</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Check-in time: <strong>3pm</strong></li>
<li>Check-out time: <strong>11am</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>A local tourist tax of approx. CHF 5.25 per person per night is payable locally (children aged 12-15 years pay a reduced rate of CHF 4.75 per person per night, and guests aged 12 and under are exempt).</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>]]></roomsDescription>
